---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PhenotypeLibrary from "../../components/PhenotypeLibrary.astro";
import SitesPicker from "../../components/SitesPicker.astro";
import DesignDiagram from "../../components/DesignDiagram.astro";
import TargetChecklist from "../../components/TargetChecklist.astro";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, "");

// Curated lists surfaced as checkboxes (matching the ACNU/SCCS/CCO/DA builders):
// tick to include, plus a free-text "custom" box.
const SUBGROUPS = [
  "Age group (e.g. ≥65 vs <65)",
  "Sex (male vs female)",
  "Comorbidity burden (e.g. CCI ≥2 vs <2)",
  "Prior cardiovascular disease",
  "Baseline disease severity",
  "Prior hospitalisation for the condition",
  "Index / calendar year (before vs after a cut-point)",
  "Baseline risk score (high vs low)",
];
// Common covariate groups / exclusion criteria, offered as quick-add chips.
const COV_TYPES = ["Demographics (age, sex)", "Comorbidities (CCI)", "Comedications", "Disease severity", "Prior healthcare use", "Labs / vitals", "Frailty", "Socioeconomic status"];
const EXCL_TYPES = ["Prior outcome event", "Competing diagnosis", "Prior exposure (washout)", "Contraindication", "Pregnancy", "End-stage disease", "Short enrolment"];

// Events that create informative (artificial) censoring, each weighted by IPCW.
// Weights are fitted separately per arm; each event maps to the assigned strategy.
const IPCW_REASONS = [
  "Death",
  "Treatment discontinuation",
  "Switch to the comparator / another drug",
  "Add-on of another therapy",
  "Loss to follow-up / disenrolment",
];
const SENSITIVITY = [
  "On-treatment (per-protocol analogue): censor at discontinuation (>90-day gap) or switch",
  "Shorter / longer grace period",
  "Weight truncation at 1st / 99th percentile",
  "Restrict outcomes to inpatient / emergency records",
  "Negative-control outcome",
  "E-value for unmeasured confounding",
  "Competing-risk (death) handling",
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Clone-Censor-Weight (CCW) protocol — Daniel Tsai"
  description="A free, in-browser protocol builder for the clone-censor-weight (sequential trial / grace-period) approach to target-trial emulation, with one-click Word / Markdown export."
>
  <header class="relative bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-50 via-white to-brand-100/40 border-b border-slate-200 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
      <p class="uppercase tracking-widest text-xs text-brand-600 font-semibold mb-2">Protocol Generator · CCW</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900">Clone-Censor-Weight protocol</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-base text-slate-600 max-w-3xl">
        Draft a target-trial-emulation protocol for treatment strategies that are only distinguishable
        <em>after</em> time zero — grace periods, sustained use, treat-to-target. Cloning + artificial censoring +
        inverse-probability-of-censoring weights (IPCW) remove the immortal-time and selection bias that a naïve
        analysis introduces. Everything runs in your browser.
      </p>
      <a class="mt-4 inline-block text-sm text-brand-700 hover:underline font-semibold" href={`${base}/tools/protocol-generator`}>← All designs</a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8">
    <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[1fr,1fr] items-start">
      <!-- Form -->
      <form id="form" class="space-y-6">
        <fieldset class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 space-y-4">
          <legend class="px-2 text-sm font-bold text-brand-700">1 · Identity</legend>
          <label class="block"><span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-700 font-semibold">Study title</span>
            <input name="title" placeholder="e.g. Early vs deferred anticoagulation after ischaemic stroke: a clone-censor-weight emulation" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-lg border border-slate-300 p-2 text-sm" /></label>
          <label class="block"><span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-700 font-semibold">Data source(s)</span>
            <input name="data" placeholder="e.g. Taiwan NHIRD (2010–2020), linked to the National Death Registry" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-lg border border-slate-300 p-2 text-sm" /></label>
          <SitesPicker target="data" />
        </fieldset>

        <fieldset class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 space-y-4">
          <legend class="px-2 text-sm font-bold text-brand-700">2 · Causal question</legend>
          <div>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
              <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-700 font-semibold">Population</span>
              <button type="button" data-open-library data-category="indications" data-target-name="population" class="text-[11px] text-brand-700 font-semibold hover:underline">📚 Library</button>
            </div>
            <input name="population" placeholder="e.g. Adults ≥ 18 with a first ischaemic stroke and atrial fibrillation" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-lg border border-slate-300 p-2 text-sm" />
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
              <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-700 font-semibold">Outcome</span>
              <button type="button" data-open-library data-category="outcomes" data-target-name="outcome" class="text-[11px] text-brand-700 font-semibold hover:underline">📚 Library</button>
            </div>
            <input name="outcome" placeholder="e.g. Recurrent stroke or systemic embolism within 90 days" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-lg border border-slate-300 p-2 text-sm" />
          </div>
        </fieldset>

        <fieldset class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 space-y-4">
          <legend class="px-2 text-sm font-bold text-brand-700">3 · Time zero &amp; strategies</legend>
          <label class="block"><span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-700 font-semibold">Time zero (must be compatible with every strategy)</span>
            <input name="timezero" placeholder="e.g. Day of stroke admission (all patients eligible for either strategy)" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-lg border border-slate-300 p-2 text-sm" /></label>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-[1fr_auto] gap-3">
            <label class="block"><span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-700 font-semibold">Strategy A</span>
              <input name="stratA" placeholder="e.g. Initiate anticoagulation within the grace period" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-lg border border-slate-300 p-2 text-sm" /></label>
            <label class="block"><span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-700 font-semibold">Grace period (days)</span>
              <input type="number" name="grace" value="14" min="0" step="1" class="mt-1 w-28 rounded-lg border border-slate-300 p-2 text-sm" /></label>
          </div>
          <label class="block"><span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-700 font-semibold">Strategy B</span>
            <input name="stratB" placeholder="e.g. Do not initiate anticoagulation during the grace period (deferred)" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-lg border border-slate-300 p-2 text-sm" /></label>
        </fieldset>

        <fieldset class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 space-y-4">
          <legend class="px-2 text-sm font-bold text-brand-700">4 · Censoring &amp; weights</legend>
          <label class="block"><span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-700 font-semibold">Deviation / censoring rule</span>
            <textarea name="censor" rows="3" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-lg border border-slate-300 p-2 text-sm" placeholder="e.g. A clone is artificially censored when its data first become incompatible with the assigned strategy: in the 'initiate' arm, if no anticoagulant is dispensed by the end of the grace period; in the 'deferred' arm, at the first dispensing during the grace period."></textarea></label>
          <label class="block"><span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-700 font-semibold">IPCW covariates (baseline + time-varying)</span>
            <textarea name="ipcw" rows="3" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-lg border border-slate-300 p-2 text-sm" placeholder="e.g. Age, sex, CHA₂DS₂-VASc, HAS-BLED, stroke severity (NIHSS proxy), renal function, concomitant antiplatelets, time-varying bleeding events and procedures."></textarea></label>
          <div>
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-700 font-semibold">Censoring events weighted by IPCW</span>
            <div class="mt-1.5 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-x-4 gap-y-1">
              {IPCW_REASONS.map((r, i) => (
                <label class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs text-slate-700">
                  <input type="checkbox" name="ipcwReasonsPick" value={r} checked={i < 3} class="mt-0.5 rounded border-slate-400 text-brand-700 focus:ring-brand-500" />
                  <span>{r}</span>
                </label>
              ))}
            </div>
            <textarea name="ipcwReasonsCustom" rows="1" class="mt-2 w-full rounded-lg border border-slate-300 p-2 text-xs" placeholder="Custom censoring events (one per line)"></textarea>
            <p class="mt-1 text-[11px] text-slate-400">Weights are estimated <strong>separately for the treatment and control arms</strong>; each event maps to the assigned strategy.</p>
          </div>
          <label class="block"><span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-700 font-semibold">Inclusion look-back (days)</span>
            <input type="number" name="incllookback" value="365" min="0" step="1" class="mt-1 w-32 rounded-lg border border-slate-300 p-2 text-sm" /></label>

          <div>
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-700 font-semibold">Exclusion criteria <span class="font-normal text-slate-400 normal-case">(name | look-back days, one per line)</span></span>
            <textarea name="excllist" rows="3" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-lg border border-slate-300 p-2 text-sm" placeholder="Prior outcome event | 365&#10;Competing diagnosis | 365">Prior outcome event | 365</textarea>
            <div class="mt-1.5 flex flex-wrap gap-1.5">
              {EXCL_TYPES.map((t) => (
                <button type="button" data-add-row data-target="excllist" data-name={t} class="text-[11px] rounded-full border border-slate-200 px-2 py-0.5 text-slate-600 hover:border-brand-400 hover:text-brand-700">+ {t}</button>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-700 font-semibold">Covariate types <span class="font-normal text-slate-400 normal-case">(name | look-back days, one per line)</span></span>
            <textarea name="covlist" rows="3" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-lg border border-slate-300 p-2 text-sm" placeholder="Comorbidities (CCI) | 365&#10;Comedications | 180">Comorbidities (CCI) | 365
Comedications | 180</textarea>
            <div class="mt-1.5 flex flex-wrap gap-1.5">
              {COV_TYPES.map((t) => (
                <button type="button" data-add-row data-target="covlist" data-name={t} class="text-[11px] rounded-full border border-slate-200 px-2 py-0.5 text-slate-600 hover:border-brand-400 hover:text-brand-700">+ {t}</button>
              ))}
            </div>
            <p class="mt-1 text-[11px] text-slate-400">Each exclusion / covariate line is drawn as its own labelled window in the diagram — drag its edge to adjust that look-back.</p>
          </div>
        </fieldset>

        <fieldset class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 space-y-4">
          <legend class="px-2 text-sm font-bold text-brand-700">5 · Follow-up &amp; analysis</legend>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-[1fr_auto] gap-3">
            <label class="block"><span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-700 font-semibold">Follow-up window / end of follow-up</span>
              <input name="followup" placeholder="e.g. From time zero to outcome, death, disenrolment, or 90 days (whichever first)" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-lg border border-slate-300 p-2 text-sm" /></label>
            <label class="block"><span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-700 font-semibold">Max follow-up (days)</span>
              <input type="number" name="fudays" value="90" min="1" step="1" class="mt-1 w-28 rounded-lg border border-slate-300 p-2 text-sm" /></label>
          </div>
          <label class="block"><span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-700 font-semibold">Effect measure</span>
            <select name="effect" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-lg border border-slate-300 p-2 text-sm">
              <option value="RD">Risk difference &amp; risk ratio from weighted cumulative incidence</option>
              <option value="HR">Hazard ratio from a weighted pooled logistic / Cox model</option>
              <option value="both">Both absolute (RD/RR) and relative (HR)</option>
            </select></label>
          <div>
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-700 font-semibold">Subgroup analyses (tick to perform)</span>
            <div class="mt-1.5 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-x-4 gap-y-1">
              {SUBGROUPS.map((sg, i) => (
                <label class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs text-slate-700">
                  <input type="checkbox" name="subgroupsPick" value={sg} checked={i < 4} class="mt-0.5 rounded border-slate-400 text-brand-700 focus:ring-brand-500" />
                  <span>{sg}</span>
                </label>
              ))}
            </div>
            <textarea name="subgroupsCustom" rows="2" class="mt-2 w-full rounded-lg border border-slate-300 p-2 text-xs" placeholder="Custom subgroups (one per line)"></textarea>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-700 font-semibold">Sensitivity analyses (tick to perform)</span>
            <div class="mt-1.5 grid grid-cols-1 gap-y-1">
              {SENSITIVITY.map((sn, i) => (
                <label class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs text-slate-700">
                  <input type="checkbox" name="sensitivityPick" value={sn} checked={i < 5} class="mt-0.5 rounded border-slate-400 text-brand-700 focus:ring-brand-500" />
                  <span>{sn}</span>
                </label>
              ))}
            </div>
            <textarea name="sensitivityCustom" rows="2" class="mt-2 w-full rounded-lg border border-slate-300 p-2 text-xs" placeholder="Custom sensitivity analyses (one per line)"></textarea>
          </div>
        </fieldset>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <button type="button" data-action="download-docx" class="bg-brand-700 text-white hover:bg-brand-800 font-semibold px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg text-sm">⬇ Word (.docx)</button>
          <button type="button" data-action="download-md" class="bg-white border border-brand-700 text-brand-700 hover:bg-brand-50 font-semibold px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg text-sm">⬇ Markdown</button>
          <button type="button" data-action="download-target" class="text-brand-700 hover:underline font-semibold text-sm" title="TARGET checklist (Cashin et al, JAMA 2025) mapped to this protocol.">⬇ TARGET checklist</button>
          <button type="button" data-action="copy" class="text-brand-700 hover:underline font-semibold text-sm">Copy</button>
          <button type="button" data-action="reset" class="text-slate-500 hover:text-slate-800 text-sm ml-auto">Reset</button>
        </div>
      </form>

      <!-- Preview -->
      <div class="lg:sticky lg:top-20 self-start">
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-500 font-semibold mb-2">Live protocol preview</p>
        <pre id="preview" class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-5 text-xs leading-relaxed whitespace-pre-wrap overflow-auto max-h-[70vh]"></pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-slate-900">Consistency checks <span class="text-xs font-normal text-slate-400">· target-trial 防呆</span></h2>
      <div id="checks" class="mt-3 space-y-1.5"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900">Study design diagram</h2>
      <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-slate-500">Cloning at time zero, the grace period, and follow-up under each strategy. <strong>Drag the ● handles</strong> to adjust the covariate look-back, grace, and follow-up — the fields above update automatically.</p>
      <div class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto"><div id="diagram"></div></div>
      <div id="dlegend" class="mt-3 flex flex-wrap gap-x-4 gap-y-1.5 text-xs text-slate-600"></div>
    </div>

    <PhenotypeLibrary />
    <DesignDiagram />
    <TargetChecklist />
  </section>

  <script src="https://unpkg.com/docx@8.5.0/build/index.umd.js" is:inline></script>
  <script is:inline>
    const STORAGE_KEY = "daniel.ccw-builder";
    const form = document.getElementById("form");
    const preview = document.getElementById("preview");
    const V = (n) => (form.elements[n]?.value || "").trim();
    const MV = (n) => [...form.querySelectorAll('[name="' + n + '"]:checked')].map((c) => c.value);
    const mergeList = (pick, custom) => [...(pick || []), ...String(custom || "").split(/\r?\n/).map((x) => x.trim()).filter(Boolean)];
    const parseRows = (txt) => String(txt || "").split(/\r?\n/).map((l) => l.trim()).filter(Boolean).map((l) => { const p = l.split("|"); return { name: (p[0] || "").trim(), days: Math.max(0, parseInt(p[1]) || 0) }; }).filter((r) => r.name);
    const rowsText = (txt) => parseRows(txt).map((r) => r.name + " (" + r.days + " d)").join("; ") || "none";
    const rowsJoin = (rows) => rows.map((r) => r.name + " | " + r.days).join("\n");

    const readForm = () => ({
      title: V("title"), data: V("data"), population: V("population"), outcome: V("outcome"),
      timezero: V("timezero"), stratA: V("stratA"), stratB: V("stratB"), grace: V("grace") || "14",
      censor: V("censor"), ipcw: V("ipcw"), ipcwReasonsPick: MV("ipcwReasonsPick"), ipcwReasonsCustom: V("ipcwReasonsCustom"), incllookback: V("incllookback") || "365", excllist: V("excllist"), covlist: V("covlist"), followup: V("followup"), fudays: V("fudays") || "90", effect: V("effect"),
      subgroupsPick: MV("subgroupsPick"), subgroupsCustom: V("subgroupsCustom"), sensitivityPick: MV("sensitivityPick"), sensitivityCustom: V("sensitivityCustom"),
    });

    const esc = (x) => String(x == null ? "" : x).replace(/[&<>"']/g, (c) => ({ "&": "&amp;", "<": "&lt;", ">": "&gt;", '"': "&quot;", "'": "&#39;" }[c]));
    function renderScheme(s) {
      const grace = Math.max(0, parseInt(s.grace) || 0);
      const fu = Math.max(grace + 1, parseInt(s.fudays) || 90);
      const incl = Math.max(0, parseInt(s.incllookback) || 0);
      const exRows = parseRows(s.excllist);
      const covRows = parseRows(s.covlist);
      const wins = [];
      if (incl > 0) wins.push({ label: "Inclusion assessment", kind: "inclusion", startDay: -incl, endDay: 0, edit: { field: "incllookback", edge: "start" } });
      exRows.forEach((r, i) => wins.push({ label: r.name, kind: "exclusion", startDay: -r.days, endDay: 0, edit: { field: "excllist", edge: "start", idx: i } }));
      covRows.forEach((r, i) => wins.push({ label: r.name, kind: "lookback", startDay: -r.days, endDay: 0, edit: { field: "covlist", edge: "start", idx: i } }));
      wins.push({ label: "Follow-up", kind: "followup", startDay: 0, endDay: fu, edit: { field: "fudays", edge: "end" } });
      const bands = grace > 0 ? [{ startDay: 0, endDay: grace, label: "grace " + grace + "d", color: "#f59e0b", edit: { field: "grace", edge: "end" } }] : [];
      const onEdit = (field, day, meta) => {
        if (field === "covlist" || field === "excllist") {
          const rel = form.elements[field];
          const rows = parseRows(rel.value);
          const idx = meta && meta.idx != null ? meta.idx : 0;
          if (rows[idx]) { rows[idx].days = Math.max(5, Math.round(-day)); rel.value = rowsJoin(rows); render(); }
          return;
        }
        let v;
        if (field === "incllookback") v = Math.max(0, -day);
        else if (field === "fudays") v = Math.max(1, day);
        else if (field === "grace") v = Math.max(0, day);
        else v = Math.abs(day);
        const el = form.elements[field]; if (el) el.value = Math.round(v);
        render();
      };
      window.renderDesignDiagram(document.getElementById("diagram"), document.getElementById("dlegend"), { windows: wins, bands: bands, indexLabel: "Time zero — clone into both arms", onEdit: onEdit, snap: 5 });
    }

    const or = (s, d) => (s && s.length ? s : d);
    const effectText = (e) => ({
      RD: "the risk difference and risk ratio, obtained by contrasting weighted cumulative-incidence (risk) curves at the end of follow-up",
      HR: "the hazard ratio from a weighted pooled logistic regression (discrete-time hazards) model with the assigned strategy as the exposure",
      both: "both absolute effects (risk difference and risk ratio from weighted cumulative-incidence curves) and the relative effect (hazard ratio from a weighted pooled logistic model)",
    })[e] || "the per-protocol effect on the risk of the outcome";

    const buildMarkdown = (s) => {
      const today = new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10);
      const A = or(s.stratA, "Strategy A — initiate treatment within the grace period");
      const B = or(s.stratB, "Strategy B — do not initiate during the grace period");
      return `# ${or(s.title, "(Untitled clone-censor-weight study)")}

_Study protocol · clone-censor-weight target-trial emulation · drafted ${today}_

## 1. Background and rationale
This study emulates a target trial to estimate the **per-protocol effect** of two treatment strategies that cannot be distinguished at time zero and are only defined by what happens over a **grace period** of ${s.grace} days. A conventional "as-treated at baseline" analysis would misclassify person-time and induce **immortal-time bias**; a "new-user" comparison cannot represent a *deferred / sustained* strategy. The clone-censor-weight (CCW) approach removes these biases by explicitly emulating the trial's assignment, adherence, and censoring structure (Hernán 2016; Maringe 2020).

## 2. Causal question (target trial)
Among **${or(s.population, "(population)")}**, what is the effect of **${A}** versus **${B}** on **${or(s.outcome, "(outcome)")}**?

## 3. Study design
A **clone-censor-weight** emulation of the target trial, using observational data from **${or(s.data, "(data source)")}**.

## 4. Time zero
${or(s.timezero, "(define time zero — a point at which every patient is compatible with, and eligible for, all strategies)")}. Eligibility, strategy assignment, and the start of follow-up are all aligned at time zero.

## 5. Treatment strategies
- **${A}**
- **${B}**
- **Grace period:** ${s.grace} days from time zero, during which the strategies are still compatible with the data.

## 6. Cloning
At time zero each eligible patient is **cloned** once into every strategy arm. Each clone is assigned to, and followed under, one strategy. This makes baseline covariate distributions identical across arms by construction (no baseline confounding of assignment).

## 7. Artificial censoring (deviation)
${or(s.censor, "A clone is censored when its observed data first become incompatible with its assigned strategy (e.g. failure to initiate by the end of the grace period, or initiation in the deferred arm). Administrative censoring applies at death, disenrolment, or end of study.")}

## 8. Inverse-probability-of-censoring weights (IPCW)
Because artificial censoring is informative, each clone receives a **time-varying, stabilised inverse-probability-of-censoring weight** (the inverse probability of remaining uncensored) to restore the population that would have persisted under full adherence. Censoring is modelled by pooled logistic regression over follow-up time, using baseline covariates over their look-back windows (**${rowsText(s.covlist)}**), with inclusion criteria assessed over ${s.incllookback} d and exclusions (${rowsText(s.excllist)}), together with time-varying predictors:

${(s.ipcw || "(list the baseline and time-varying predictors of deviation — e.g. age, sex, comorbidity and bleeding-risk scores, disease severity, concomitant therapy, and post-baseline events)").split(/\r?\n/).map((l) => l.trim()).filter(Boolean).map((l) => "- " + l).join("\n") || "- (covariates)"}

Separate weight models are fitted for the **treatment** and **control** arms. The events treated as informative censoring and weighted by IPCW (each mapping to the assigned strategy) are: ${mergeList(s.ipcwReasonsPick, s.ipcwReasonsCustom).join("; ") || "(none selected)"}. Weights are cumulative over follow-up and truncated at the 1st/99th percentiles.

## 9. Follow-up and outcome
${or(s.followup, "Follow-up runs from time zero until the outcome, death, disenrolment, or the end of the study period, whichever comes first.")} Outcome: **${or(s.outcome, "(outcome)")}**.

## 10. Estimand and effect measure
The primary estimand is the **per-protocol effect** (receiving and adhering to each strategy), estimated by the clone-censor-weight analysis. For comparison we also report an **as-started (intention-to-treat-analogue) effect** from a conventional analysis (Section 11). We report ${effectText(s.effect)}, with 95% confidence intervals from a **nonparametric bootstrap** (resampling patients, keeping each patient's clones together).

## 11. Statistical analysis
**Primary — clone-censor-weight (per-protocol):**
1. Clone the eligible cohort into the strategy arms and apply the censoring rule.
2. Fit the censoring model(s) and compute stabilised, time-varying IPCW.
3. Fit a **weighted pooled logistic regression** for the discrete-time hazard, with the assigned strategy, follow-up time, its quadratic term, and a strategy × time interaction; derive weighted cumulative-incidence curves.
4. Contrast the curves for the effect measure(s); obtain 95% CIs by **nonparametric bootstrap** (resampling patients).

**Comparison — conventional analysis (as-started, ITT-analogue):** start follow-up at the index date, balance the arms by **propensity-score matching** (standardised mean difference < 0.1 as the balance criterion), and handle the competing risk of death with **Fine–Gray sub-distribution** and **cause-specific Cox** models. The gap between this and the CCW estimate indexes the time-lag / immortal-time bias removed.

## 12. Subgroup analyses
${(mergeList(s.subgroupsPick, s.subgroupsCustom).length ? mergeList(s.subgroupsPick, s.subgroupsCustom) : ["(none pre-specified)"]).map((l) => "- " + l).join("\n")}

